--- OLLAMA ERROR ANALYSIS (attempt 1) ---
The RPM build failed with an `Installed (but unpackaged) file(s) found:` error. This occurs when files are copied to the `$RPM_BUILD_ROOT` during `%install`, but are not explicitly listed in the `%files` section. In openSUSE/modern RPM packaging, info pages, man pages, images, and auxiliary binaries are **not** automatically bundled; every installed path must be declared.

**Fix:**
Add the exact missing paths to the `%files` block in `gawk.spec`. You can append them directly to the existing file list:
```spec
%{_bindir}/gawkbug
%{_infodir}/gawk_api-figure1.png
%{_infodir}/gawk_api-figure2.png
%{_infodir}/gawk_api-figure3.png
%{_infodir}/gawk_array-elements.png
%{_infodir}/gawk_general-program.png
%{_infodir}/gawk_process-flow.png
%{_infodir}/gawk_statist.jpg
%{_mandir}/man1/gawkbug.1.gz
%{_mandir}/man1/pm-gawk.1.gz
```
*(If your spec does not already define these macros, using the literal `/usr/bin/`, `/usr/share/info/`, and `/usr/share/man/man1/` paths is equally valid. Ensure every single path from the error log is included; RPM will reject the package if even one file is omitted.)*
